A set stores unique values only — duplicates are automatically removed. Great for membership testing (much faster than lists) and set operations (union, intersection).

```python
tags = {"python", "code", "python", "learn"}
print(tags)  # {'python', 'code', 'learn'} — no duplicates

a = {1, 2, 3, 4}
b = {3, 4, 5, 6}
print(a & b)  # {3, 4}  — intersection
print(a | b)  # {1,2,3,4,5,6} — union
print(a - b)  # {1, 2}  — difference
```
